    <questiontext format="markdown">
      <text>**32.1 E3 Trapezium Method with f(t,y)**

Suppose that y = y(t) is the solution to the initial value problem

\\\(\displaystyle{@'diff(y,t)=dy(t,y)@}\\\), {@'y0=y0@}

Carry out two time steps of the trapezium method with a step size of {@'h = h@} so as to obtain
approximations  to \\\(y(t)\\\) for the first two time steps

\\\(y({@h@})\approx\\\) [[input:S_y1]] [[validation:S_y1]] [[feedback:y1]]

\\\(y({@2*h@})\approx\\\) [[input:S_y2]] [[validation:S_y2]] [[feedback:y2]]</text>
